---
layout: base.njk
title: Home
description: A writing portfolio featuring essays, criticism, and reported work.
---
{% set featuredArticles = articles | where("status", "featured") %}
{% set featured = featuredArticles[0] %}
{% set regularArticles = articles | where("status", "displayed") %}

<section class="intro-section">
  <div class="container intro-grid">
    <div class="intro-copy">
      <h1>{{ site.name }}</h1>
      <p class="lede">I'm a freelance writer exploring scientific discoveries and the people behind them.</p>
      <p class="intro-text">From feature stories to research explainers, I dig into the latest developments in social science and extract what matters most. My work translates big ideas into interesting stories and actionable insights.</p>
      <a class="button-link" href="#writing">Read my work</a>
    </div>
    <div class="headshot-card" aria-label="Portrait area">
      <img src="{{ site.headshot | url }}" alt="Headshot of {{ site.name }}">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% if featured %}
<section class="featured-section" aria-labelledby="featured-heading">
  <div class="container">
    
    <article class="featured-article">
      <a class="featured-image" href="{{ featured.link }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="{{ featured.photo | url }}" alt="">
      </a>
      <div class="featured-content">
        <p><time datetime="{{ featured.publicationDate }}">{{ featured.publicationDate | readableDate }}</time> | {{ featured.outlet }}</p>
        <h3><a href="{{ featured.link }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{{ featured.title }}</a></h3>
        <p>{{ featured.blurb }}</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{ featured.link }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read article</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<section class="writing-section" id="writing" aria-labelledby="writing-heading">
  <div class="container">
    
    <div class="article-grid">
      {% for article in regularArticles %}
      <article class="article-card">
        <a class="article-image" href="{{ article.link }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <img src="{{ article.photo | url }}" alt="">
        </a>
        <div class="article-content">
        <p><time datetime="{{ article.publicationDate }}">{{ article.publicationDate | readableDate }}</time> | {{ article.outlet }}</p>          
        <h3><a href="{{ article.link }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{{ article.title }}</a></h3>
          <p>{{ article.blurb }}</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

     <p class="see-all" style="text-align: center;">
      <a href="/all" class="see-all-link">See all articles →</a>
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section" id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container about-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Me</p>
    <h2 id="about-heading">Allow me to introduce myself.</h2>
    <p>I've been writing for as long as I can remember. I started my career writing technical copy for SEO content mills as a teenager, and I quickly got hooked. In college, I wrote email newsletters for the coding education company <a href="https://levelup.video/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Level Up Tutorials</a> and investigated local history questions for Central Ohio's NPR newsroom, <a href="https://www.wosu.org/people/sydney-sauer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WOSU Public Media</a>.
    <br><br>
    Now, as a sociology PhD student at Harvard University, I'm still writing. My monthly column at <a href="https://filtermag.org/author/sydney-sauer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Filter Magazine</a> covers the latest scientific studies on harm reduction and overdose prevention. I'm also a freelance writer for <a href="https://gsas.harvard.edu/news" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Harvard's Graduate School of Arts and Sciences</a>, where I write interview-driven profiles of notable students and alumni.
    <br><br>
    Because I just can't get enough, my PhD research also focuses on science communication media, investigating both how it's created and how people respond to it.
    <br><br>
    Want to connect? You can reach me at <a href="mailto:sydneysauer@fas.harvard.edu">sydneysauer@fas.harvard.edu</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>